http://www.oie.int/wahis_2/public/wahid.php/Reviewreport/Review?page_refer=MapFullEventReport&reportid=18146


Peste des petits ruminants, Liberia
-----------------------------------
Information received on [and dated] 16 Jul 2015 from Dr Seklau Elizabeth Wiles, Director, National Livestock Bureau, Ministry of Agriculture, Monrovia, Liberia.

Summary
Report type: Immediate notification
Date of start of the event: 20 Apr 2015
Date of confirmation of the event: 10 Jul 2015
Reason for notification: 1st occurrence of a listed disease
Manifestation of disease: clinical disease
Causal agent: peste des petits ruminants virus
Nature of diagnosis: clinical, laboratory (basic), laboratory (advanced), necropsy
This event pertains to the whole country

New outbreaks (5)
Outbreak 1: Kimon, Nimba
Date of start of the outbreak: 20 Apr 2015
Outbreak status: continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit: village
Affected animals:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Goats / - / 500 / 485 / - / -
Sheep / - / 250 / 195/ - / -

Outbreak 2: Gbonie, Nimba
Date of start of the outbreak: 1 Jul 2015
Outbreak status: continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit: village
Affected animals:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Sheep/goats / - / - / - / - / -

Outbreak 3: Leagbala, Nimba
Date of start of the outbreak: 1 Jun 2015
Outbreak status: continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit: village
Affected animals:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Goats / - / 60 / 60 / - / -

Outbreak 4: Gbalayee, Nimba
Date of start of the outbreak: 1 Jun 2015
