Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[Liberia borders with Sierra Leone, Guinea and Cote d'Ivoire, regions where the disease is reported as present. See OIE WAHID's database section on "detailed country(ies) disease incidence" (Note: To see the information, select the disease and region of interest).

Although the disease is present in the region, this is the 1st occurrence of peste des petits ruminants reported officially by Liberia.

See commentaries in ProMED-mail posts 20150707.3489701 and 20150704.3485411.

See map of Liberia at http://www.nationsonline.org/oneworld/map/liberia-map.htm. - Mod.CRD

A HealthMap/ProMED-mail map can be accessed at: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=3516442,2686.]
